RATTO, Rodolfo, Genova, Milan, Italy;  Lugano, Switzerland;  Milan

 

(1864-1949) born to an old Genoese family, began his career in

1893 in Genova, moved to Milan in 1910 to become the leading coin

dealer in Italy.  In 1921 he moved to his villa in Lugano, but

later returned to Milan.    [Italo Vecchi]

           Obituary and Bibliography in Rivista Italiana di Numismatica, 1949, pp. 85-88.

 

* All Auction catalogues to 1920, and some Lists to 1944, are analysed in minute detail in the catalogue of the disastrous auction of the Domenico Rossi library, Varesi 45, 20 April 2005, lots L2839-L2913.

ROLLIN, C., Paris;  London

 

Rollin & Feuardent claimed to be the world's oldest proper coin

dealership.  Founded by Charles-Louis Rollin (1777-1853) who

began his career as a money-changer in the galleries of the

Palais Royal, published his first coin sales list in 1811, and

moved in the 1840's to premises at 12 rue Vivienne opposite the

Bibliothèque Royale.  The business passed in the third generation

into the hands of Felix Feuardent (1819-1907), a provincial

librarian who became a partner in 1859, and in 1860 married the

daughter of Charles-Louis' son,  Camile.  As scholars, dealers and

auctioneers they became pre-eminent in fin de siècle Paris, running a

branch in London as well. [Italo Vecchi]
